WEBVTT

00:01.044 --> 00:03.133
♪

00:03.177 --> 00:05.179
Iris: <i>Once upon a time,</i>

00:05.222 --> 00:07.007
<i>there was
the world as we knew it.</i>

00:07.050 --> 00:10.836
[Crowd cheers]

00:10.880 --> 00:14.057
<i>A world with pets and homes,</i>

00:14.101 --> 00:16.625
<i>grocery stores and hospitals,</i>

00:16.668 --> 00:18.801
<i>jobs and weekends.</i>

00:18.844 --> 00:20.933
[Horns honking]

00:24.198 --> 00:26.069
<i>And then everything changed.</i>

00:26.113 --> 00:27.810
[Baby crying]

00:27.853 --> 00:31.292
<i>The people died
and then returned,</i>

00:31.335 --> 00:34.860
<i>neither living nor dead,</i>

00:34.904 --> 00:40.692
<i>the love they felt for anyone or anything erased from memory,</i>

00:40.736 --> 00:45.088
<i>replaced by a hunger
that could never be satisfied.</i>

00:45.132 --> 00:46.916
<i>Everything we had counted on --</i>

00:46.959 --> 00:49.397
<i>our advances in technology,</i>

00:49.440 --> 00:51.181
<i>our feats of engineering --</i>

00:51.225 --> 00:52.878
<i>could not save us.</i>

00:52.922 --> 00:54.489
[Walkers growling]

00:54.532 --> 00:56.186
<i>Roads crumbled</i>

00:56.230 --> 00:59.407
<i>and cities fell
into heaps of rubble.</i>

00:59.450 --> 01:02.105
♪

01:02.149 --> 01:05.717
<i>And for those of us
born right before?</i>

01:05.761 --> 01:08.503
<i>The end of the world
was our beginning.</i>

01:13.769 --> 01:18.904
♪

01:23.344 --> 01:26.347
Hey, stop.
Stay where you are.

01:26.390 --> 01:28.871
Why are you spying on us?I mean it, get back!

01:28.914 --> 01:30.264
Hey, don't get any closer.Hope, stop!

01:30.307 --> 01:32.135
Don't get any closer.

01:32.179 --> 01:33.441
Why don't you just drop your
weapon and we'll talk about it?

01:33.484 --> 01:34.572
No.
No, no way.

01:34.616 --> 01:35.747
Hey, stay where you are,big guy.

01:35.791 --> 01:37.140
Why?
You think you can take him?

01:37.184 --> 01:38.359
This'll poke an eye outas good as anything.

01:38.402 --> 01:39.664
Wanna come closer
and find out?

01:39.708 --> 01:42.058
Hey, leave her alone.

01:42.102 --> 01:43.886
Okay, fine.

01:43.929 --> 01:45.148
Here's how
it's gonna go.

01:45.192 --> 01:47.585
You stay where you are,and I split.

01:47.629 --> 01:50.110
[Rustling]

01:50.153 --> 01:53.722
[Insects chirping]

01:53.765 --> 01:55.376
You candrop that weapon now.

01:58.248 --> 01:59.597
[Gun cocks]

01:59.641 --> 02:02.078
Alright, let me save youthe mental exercise.

02:04.602 --> 02:08.563
Your chances --not lookin' that good.

02:10.478 --> 02:11.827
Go on.

02:11.870 --> 02:13.263
[Stick thuds]

02:13.307 --> 02:16.266
Elton, Silas,check the perimeter.

02:16.310 --> 02:18.138
See if he's got
any friends.

02:27.016 --> 02:29.192
Iris, search him.

02:29.236 --> 02:30.628
[Scoffs]

02:35.764 --> 02:37.418
Look,
I already told you.

02:39.681 --> 02:41.291
I'm alone.

02:43.946 --> 02:47.210
Look,
you wanna know the truth?

02:47.254 --> 02:50.039
I was in the bushes taking
a leak when I heard voices.

02:50.082 --> 02:52.737
Hope: What, so you decided
to rob us?

02:55.349 --> 02:57.568
Nothing.
Huh.

02:57.612 --> 03:00.310
Where is your stuff?
Your food?

03:00.354 --> 03:02.094
I-I don't have stuff.

03:02.138 --> 03:05.402
I don't have anything.

03:05.446 --> 03:06.969
Silas:No signs of anyone else.

03:07.012 --> 03:10.277
Just him.

03:10.320 --> 03:12.844
Hm.

03:12.888 --> 03:15.107
What is your name?

03:15.151 --> 03:18.676
Percy.

03:18.720 --> 03:20.678
Are you hungry,
Percy?

03:24.813 --> 03:28.208
[Spoon scraping]

03:32.516 --> 03:34.692
Seemed like
nice enough guys.

03:34.736 --> 03:35.998
Mike and Tony.

03:36.041 --> 03:38.740
Mike had this
kind of biker vibe --

03:38.783 --> 03:43.135
you know, tats,
full sleeves on both arms.

03:43.179 --> 03:45.616
And Tony, not so much.

03:45.660 --> 03:48.489
I don't think they kneweach other before shit went bad.

03:48.532 --> 03:49.925
Maybe they did.

03:49.968 --> 03:51.448
They bickered like
an old married couple.

03:51.492 --> 03:54.364
You know, everything --
which route to take,

03:54.408 --> 03:56.845
how much fish one guy
had eaten, you know.

03:56.888 --> 03:58.542
Blah, blah, blah.

04:01.545 --> 04:03.982
Like I said, they seemed
like nice enough guys.

04:06.333 --> 04:08.596
Well, they robbed my ass.

04:08.639 --> 04:11.468
When did
that happen?

04:11.512 --> 04:12.948
Couple days ago.

04:12.991 --> 04:14.341
We'd gone to this settlement

04:14.384 --> 04:16.778
we heard was friendly
to newcomers.

04:16.821 --> 04:18.475
We heard wrong.

04:21.478 --> 04:24.873
Maybe they just
didn't like you.

04:24.916 --> 04:28.790
Left in a hurry, found a place
to camp down, fell asleep.

04:28.833 --> 04:31.401
When I woke up, they were gone,and so was my stuff.

04:35.623 --> 04:37.668
Guess they finally agreed
on something.

04:40.367 --> 04:41.585
That's why I'm here.

04:41.629 --> 04:43.805
To eat our beans?

04:43.848 --> 04:46.329
I think they're at the abandoned
town down the road.

04:46.373 --> 04:49.854
Andersonville.

04:49.898 --> 04:52.292
I'm going back there
to get back what's mine.

04:54.337 --> 04:57.166
Hey,
can I give you some advice?

04:57.209 --> 05:00.125
Just be grateful they left you
with your life and move on.

05:03.868 --> 05:07.263
This isn't
a vigilante-type deal.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.918
And it ain't about the principleof it all, either.

05:12.442 --> 05:14.314
Some things
just can't be replaced.

05:14.357 --> 05:19.493
♪

05:19.536 --> 05:21.146
I get that.

05:21.190 --> 05:29.067
♪

05:29.111 --> 05:31.287
[Fence rattles]

05:38.163 --> 05:41.036
[Grunts]

05:41.079 --> 05:43.517
Just taking some
extra precaution

05:43.560 --> 05:46.171
in case this kid's lyingand his buddies show.

05:48.696 --> 05:51.525
Maybe we could give him
some of our supplies now

05:51.568 --> 05:53.178
and he could go.

05:53.222 --> 05:57.835
[Laughter,
indistinct conversation]

05:57.879 --> 06:00.142
Doesn't really seem
in a rush to leave.

06:04.668 --> 06:06.714
Percy: So, I'm totally screwed,right?

06:06.757 --> 06:08.063
I'm in Wyoming.

06:08.106 --> 06:10.108
It's the middle of February,right?

06:10.152 --> 06:11.719
I'm trudging down I-90,

06:11.762 --> 06:14.374
just walking through2 feet of snow.

06:14.417 --> 06:16.506
I'm just prayingfor some sort of shelter

06:16.550 --> 06:18.769
so I can wait out the storm.

06:18.813 --> 06:20.423
That's when I hear 'em.

06:20.467 --> 06:24.645
Moans so load you could feelthe vibrations in the show.

06:24.688 --> 06:28.083
Now, I'd seen of herdsof has-beens before,

06:28.126 --> 06:30.390
but nothing like this.

06:30.433 --> 06:34.045
So I panicked.I'm yankin' on every car door.

06:34.089 --> 06:35.699
No deal.
Rusted shut.

06:35.743 --> 06:36.918
Did you run?

06:36.961 --> 06:38.572
I'm ona freakin' overpass.

06:38.615 --> 06:40.443
So, what did you do?

06:40.487 --> 06:45.970
S-So, I, uh, sat on a car roofand waited.

06:46.014 --> 06:47.319
Bullshit.I did.

06:47.363 --> 06:50.671
I told myself, you know,world was screwed up,

06:50.714 --> 06:55.066
so, uh, why fight so hardto live in it, right?

06:55.110 --> 06:58.505
♪

06:58.548 --> 07:00.028
Shut my eyes.

07:00.071 --> 07:02.596
As the has-beens got closer,I could hear 'em,

07:02.639 --> 07:04.641
snow under their feet,

07:04.685 --> 07:08.079
feel 'embumpin' into the car.

07:08.123 --> 07:10.647
Mm.

07:10.691 --> 07:12.301
I braced myself
for the end.

07:12.344 --> 07:16.392
♪

07:16.436 --> 07:17.959
Nothin'.

07:18.002 --> 07:23.268
♪

07:23.312 --> 07:24.922
I opened my eyes.

07:24.966 --> 07:27.142
♪

07:27.185 --> 07:29.797
It's a herd of bison.

07:29.840 --> 07:33.104
200 of 'em, just crossin'the freakin' overpass.

07:33.148 --> 07:35.672
[Laughs]

07:35.716 --> 07:37.457
It was the mostbeautiful thing I ever seen.

07:37.500 --> 07:39.981
And after that, I was like,
"Screw death.

07:40.024 --> 07:42.200
I'm -- I'm --
I'm here for this."

07:42.244 --> 07:43.637
Geez!
That's wild.

07:43.680 --> 07:47.641
I mean, just to see
something like that.

07:47.684 --> 07:49.120
Yeah.

07:49.164 --> 07:52.384
Out here, the, uh --the real is surreal, you know.

07:52.428 --> 07:56.476
That spring, I saw a, uh --a Ferris wheel in Orlando

07:56.519 --> 07:59.609
that had been turnedinto pelican nests.

07:59.653 --> 08:01.568
200 bison.

08:01.611 --> 08:04.005
That --
That's amazing!

08:04.048 --> 08:06.007
Wait.

08:06.050 --> 08:08.488
You saw the bison that winter?

08:08.531 --> 08:10.968
How'd you get from Wyoming
to Florida in a couple months?

08:11.012 --> 08:13.362
That's impossible.

08:13.405 --> 08:15.233
Did I say that?

08:15.277 --> 08:16.844
That must've been
the year after.

08:16.887 --> 08:18.541
No one stole your supplies.I'm -- Look, I misspoke.

08:18.585 --> 08:21.588
No, you didn't.

08:21.631 --> 08:24.286
Okay, Hope, does it really
make a difference?

08:24.329 --> 08:26.418
You didn't get your food
and your pack stolen.

08:26.462 --> 08:29.073
Hey, hey, hey.
Keep it down.

08:29.117 --> 08:30.727
They stole your car.

08:30.771 --> 08:32.860
That's how you got from
Wyoming to Florida so fast.

08:32.903 --> 08:34.470
That's what they took,
right?

08:34.514 --> 08:38.605
♪

08:38.648 --> 08:40.781
[Chuckles]

08:40.824 --> 08:42.783
Um, is this true?

08:45.699 --> 08:47.657
'Bout a year ago,

08:47.701 --> 08:50.965
I saw a truckthat had skidded onto the ice.

08:51.008 --> 08:53.707
Must've just happened, becausethe engine was still running,

08:53.750 --> 08:58.494
and the -- the driverwas going from, you know,

08:58.538 --> 09:00.888
"once was"
to has-been.

09:00.931 --> 09:02.193
Silas: Why'd you lie?

09:02.237 --> 09:05.719
Coulda just told us
they stole your car.

09:05.762 --> 09:07.416
It's like telling youthere's buried treasure

09:07.459 --> 09:12.595
and expecting you notto go digging for it.

09:12.639 --> 09:15.467
It's not just a working truck,okay?

09:15.511 --> 09:17.905
It's carrying barrelsof refined fuel.

09:17.948 --> 09:20.995
It's likewinning the jackpot.

09:21.038 --> 09:23.084
What if we help you
get it back?

09:23.127 --> 09:26.566
Iris.
For a price.

09:26.609 --> 09:27.915
We help you get
your truck back,

09:27.958 --> 09:29.656
you drive us
where we need to go.

09:29.699 --> 09:31.919
♪

09:31.962 --> 09:33.268
Where's that?

09:33.311 --> 09:34.617
Does it matter?

09:34.661 --> 09:37.228
No.
There's no way that those guys

09:37.272 --> 09:38.969
are givin' up that thing
without a fight.

09:39.013 --> 09:40.405
Alright?
I -- It's too risky.

09:40.449 --> 09:41.755
With a truck,
we avoid empties.

09:41.798 --> 09:43.321
We get there
in half the time.

09:43.365 --> 09:45.323
We don't have to worry about
running out of supplies.

09:45.367 --> 09:47.587
Shouldn't we wait
for Huck?

09:47.630 --> 09:49.197
For backup,
you know?

09:49.240 --> 09:51.852
Those guys could be gone
by then, along with the truck.

09:51.895 --> 09:54.028
♪

09:54.071 --> 09:56.247
Two of them.

09:56.291 --> 09:58.032
Six of us.

09:58.075 --> 10:01.296
But if they got guns, doesn'tmatter how many of us there are.

10:01.339 --> 10:04.255
Well, I --I've never seen any guns.

10:04.299 --> 10:06.475
I mean, that wouldn't be
the first thing

10:06.518 --> 10:07.911
that they hid from me,but...

10:07.955 --> 10:11.045
We either get hurt,
or we have to hurt them.

10:11.088 --> 10:13.177
Elton: We do have the element
of surprise on our side.

10:13.221 --> 10:14.657
If we use that to our advantage,

10:14.701 --> 10:17.138
it increases our chances
significantly.

10:17.181 --> 10:19.357
How do I know you guyswon't just take my truck

10:19.401 --> 10:20.402
and leave me
in the dust?

10:20.445 --> 10:23.361
We won't.

10:23.405 --> 10:25.755
She gave you her word.

10:25.799 --> 10:27.975
Out here, that doesn't meanmuch, big fella.

10:28.018 --> 10:31.326
♪

10:31.369 --> 10:34.198
Please.

10:34.242 --> 10:36.766
We need to get
where we're going fast.

10:36.810 --> 10:39.595
It could be the difference
between our dad living and...

10:39.639 --> 10:45.166
♪

10:45.209 --> 10:47.168
Look.

10:47.211 --> 10:48.386
If we wanted to steal
your truck,

10:48.430 --> 10:49.953
we would just take it,

10:49.997 --> 10:52.652
with or without
your help.

10:52.695 --> 10:55.350
You already told us
where it was.

10:55.393 --> 10:57.134
So...

10:57.178 --> 11:00.268
♪

11:00.311 --> 11:02.923
How 'bout,

11:02.966 --> 11:06.361
at dawn,

11:06.404 --> 11:09.451
we go find ourselves
a truck?

11:23.160 --> 11:25.423
♪

11:25.467 --> 11:27.556
[Spray-paint spraying]

11:45.226 --> 11:53.974
♪

11:54.017 --> 11:55.540
[Camera shutter clicks]

11:55.584 --> 12:00.720
♪

12:05.028 --> 12:08.640
What was she like?

12:08.684 --> 12:11.382
She was great.

12:11.426 --> 12:13.428
Sunday mornings,she'd make French toast,

12:13.471 --> 12:15.212
sing alongwith the record player.

12:15.256 --> 12:17.388
Her voice sounded likea bronchial infection

12:17.432 --> 12:18.999
set to music, but...

12:19.042 --> 12:21.262
still like her versionof "Tiny Dancer" the best.

12:21.305 --> 12:22.959
Wait.

12:23.003 --> 12:25.614
You were named after
Elton John?

12:25.657 --> 12:26.876
He's an icon!

12:26.920 --> 12:29.139
That's very cool.

12:29.183 --> 12:31.402
My mom
was the coolest.

12:31.446 --> 12:33.491
This helped me
get to know her.

12:33.535 --> 12:36.103
She saw death and decayas no better or worse

12:36.146 --> 12:37.757
than any of
life's cycles.

12:37.800 --> 12:40.411
She wasn't
afraid of it.

12:40.455 --> 12:42.544
Um, what are you gonna
do with it?

12:42.587 --> 12:45.939
The book, I mean.
Like, after you finish it.

12:45.982 --> 12:47.897
I'd like to pass it on.

12:47.941 --> 12:50.813
You know, so it could helpsomebody with the big questions.

12:50.857 --> 12:53.424
Help 'em feel less confusedand alone,

12:53.468 --> 12:54.817
just like
it has done for me.

12:54.861 --> 12:57.689
That way, my motherwill never be forgotten.

12:57.733 --> 13:00.127
I'll help you finish it.

13:00.170 --> 13:01.519
Yeah,
collecting samples,

13:01.563 --> 13:04.609
taking picture of worms
and stuff.

13:04.653 --> 13:07.612
Whatever you need
to finish it.

13:07.656 --> 13:08.788
Thank you.

13:08.831 --> 13:14.576
♪

13:14.619 --> 13:17.013
Hold on.You've read "Hamlet"?

13:17.057 --> 13:20.103
Percy: Thanks. The surprise in
your voice is very flattering.

13:20.147 --> 13:22.889
Hey, big guy, I can fix
that boot for ya.

13:22.932 --> 13:26.022
Little bit of charcoal
and tree sap makes glue.

13:26.066 --> 13:27.807
Mm-hmm.

13:27.850 --> 13:29.721
Do you knowany other good tricks?

13:29.765 --> 13:32.289
We've only been outof the University like a month.

13:32.333 --> 13:33.987
Yeah, what's the deal
with that?

13:34.030 --> 13:37.381
You guys had hot showers
and food and beds.

13:37.425 --> 13:40.428
If I had a cushy situation
like that, I'd never leave.

13:40.471 --> 13:42.865
Yeah, it, uh,
wasn't as good as it sounds.

13:46.173 --> 13:49.480
The University, it waslike a bubble, you know?

13:49.524 --> 13:51.482
Hm.

13:51.526 --> 13:52.962
Well, you're not careful,
you and your bubble friends

13:53.006 --> 13:54.964
are gonna get yourselves
killed out here.

13:55.008 --> 13:58.925
Um, my friends and I made itthrough an inferno of empties

13:58.968 --> 14:01.841
and crossed
the Mississippi.

14:01.884 --> 14:05.627
You were robbed -- oh! --and started a fight with a twig.

14:05.670 --> 14:08.151
Between us,think I'm doin' just fine.

14:10.197 --> 14:11.851
Whatever you say.

14:16.333 --> 14:19.946
You wanna know the real reasonwe're out here?

14:19.989 --> 14:22.209
My dad.

14:22.252 --> 14:24.341
He was sentto work on a project,

14:24.385 --> 14:28.737
but he's in trouble.

14:28.780 --> 14:30.870
We're out here
to find him.

14:30.913 --> 14:32.523
Save him.

14:34.482 --> 14:39.182
Ah, you're lucky.
You still got somebody to save.

14:39.226 --> 14:41.532
That's rare.

14:41.576 --> 14:43.186
Even more
than a working car.

14:45.928 --> 14:47.843
Let me guess.Either you joined me back here

14:47.887 --> 14:50.585
for my dazzlingconversational skills,

14:50.628 --> 14:55.155
or you really don't
like that kid.

14:55.198 --> 14:57.374
I don't.
Mm.

14:57.418 --> 14:59.855
I don't know why
anybody else does.

14:59.899 --> 15:02.118
Well...

15:02.162 --> 15:04.381
We can't always control
who we like.

15:04.425 --> 15:06.253
♪

15:06.296 --> 15:08.037
Come on.

15:14.957 --> 15:21.703
♪

15:21.746 --> 15:24.619
[Thunder rumbles]

15:43.290 --> 15:52.603
♪

15:52.647 --> 15:54.736
[Engine revs]

16:04.311 --> 16:13.798
♪

16:13.842 --> 16:15.235
That's them.

16:15.278 --> 16:17.019
That's my truck.

16:17.063 --> 16:18.455
Come on.

16:18.499 --> 16:25.114
♪

16:25.158 --> 16:26.898
Iris: So, how are we supposed
to get it?

16:26.942 --> 16:28.596
Maybe we wait
until it's dark?

16:28.639 --> 16:30.902
I don't see
any movement.

16:30.946 --> 16:32.295
But they've got
to be here.

16:32.339 --> 16:35.777
I mean, they were just
driving the truck.

16:35.820 --> 16:39.085
We need eyes on both of thembefore we do anything.

16:39.128 --> 16:40.782
No, I say
we smash and grab.

16:40.825 --> 16:42.175
Move fast,
we can be on the road

16:42.218 --> 16:43.567
before they even know
what's happening.

16:43.611 --> 16:45.178
You don't have the keys.

16:45.221 --> 16:46.527
I can hot-wire it
in under a minute.

16:46.570 --> 16:50.487
I don't...
We shouldn't do this.

16:50.531 --> 16:53.055
We are wasting time.
We need to make a decision.

16:53.099 --> 16:56.450
[Thunder rumbles]

16:56.493 --> 16:58.234
[Sighs]

16:58.278 --> 17:00.932
Rest of you stay here.

17:00.976 --> 17:02.586
I'll cover Percy.

17:11.421 --> 17:18.472
♪

17:18.515 --> 17:21.475
[Truck door opens]

17:21.518 --> 17:23.912
Percy: Holy shit.

17:23.955 --> 17:25.479
What is it?

17:25.522 --> 17:33.748
♪

17:33.791 --> 17:35.315
Tony.

17:35.358 --> 17:36.881
♪

17:40.320 --> 17:43.192
Guess the bickering
got worse.

17:43.236 --> 17:45.847
Yeah. We're gonna haveto get outta here.

17:45.890 --> 17:48.328
Chill.
We are gettin' outta here.

17:48.371 --> 17:49.459
In this.

17:49.503 --> 17:53.507
[Thumps]

17:53.550 --> 17:54.595
Damn it.

17:54.638 --> 17:56.118
What?
What is it?

17:56.162 --> 17:58.381
They bolted a plateover the ignition wires.

17:58.425 --> 18:06.520
♪

18:06.563 --> 18:07.782
Shit.
[Grunts]

18:07.825 --> 18:09.871
What's wrong?

18:09.914 --> 18:11.307
Oh, shit.

18:11.351 --> 18:13.135
Oh, my.
Hey!

18:13.179 --> 18:16.356
I told you to wait
on the other side.

18:16.399 --> 18:18.053
Let's go, alright?This is not happening.

18:18.097 --> 18:19.881
No keys,
but I got this.

18:19.924 --> 18:21.491
Hey! What the hell do you think
you're doin'?

18:21.535 --> 18:23.363
Getting those keys back.

18:23.406 --> 18:24.929
Don't be an idiot.

18:24.973 --> 18:26.931
You all wanna leave,then leave.

18:26.975 --> 18:28.542
I got nothing
left to lose.

18:29.978 --> 18:32.154
[Thunder rumbling]

18:32.198 --> 18:33.938
We're going back
to the campsite.

18:37.290 --> 18:38.769
Hey.
Are you crazy?

18:38.813 --> 18:41.076
We said we'd help.

18:41.120 --> 18:43.992
I'm going to.

18:44.035 --> 18:45.602
Stop.

18:47.691 --> 18:49.084
I'll go.

18:49.128 --> 18:50.564
Watch this.

18:50.607 --> 18:51.739
It would be prudent
to have a lookout

18:51.782 --> 18:53.349
at the front
of the building

18:53.393 --> 18:55.177
in case Mike isn't there
and he decides to come back.

18:55.221 --> 18:57.919
Alright.I'll come with you guys.

18:57.962 --> 18:59.312
As backup.

18:59.355 --> 19:00.965
[Bags clatter]

19:01.009 --> 19:04.099
You twokeep an eye on our gear.

19:04.143 --> 19:06.275
Come on.

19:19.984 --> 19:26.774
♪

19:26.817 --> 19:28.471
That's the only one
not boarded up.

19:28.515 --> 19:34.738
♪

19:34.782 --> 19:36.305
Stay here.

19:41.658 --> 19:46.968
♪

19:47.011 --> 19:49.275
[Hand slams]

19:49.318 --> 19:57.108
♪

19:57.152 --> 19:58.632
Thought
I heard something.

19:58.675 --> 20:00.634
In the back.

20:00.677 --> 20:02.026
Flanking maneuver.

20:02.070 --> 20:04.638
You go left,
I go right.

20:04.681 --> 20:06.030
If Mike gets the jumpon one of us,

20:06.074 --> 20:08.250
the other comes in
from the side.

20:08.294 --> 20:09.817
Go.

20:09.860 --> 20:12.863
♪

20:14.343 --> 20:15.953
[Sighs]

20:18.129 --> 20:19.479
I can't take it.

20:19.522 --> 20:21.829
I'm going in.

20:21.872 --> 20:26.312
But you --But you promised Felix.

20:26.355 --> 20:28.009
I don't
trust that guy.

20:28.052 --> 20:31.795
We can't keep
being so afraid.

20:31.839 --> 20:33.275
How are we supposed
to save my dad

20:33.319 --> 20:36.496
if we are always waiting
for other people to save us?

20:36.539 --> 20:40.761
You talking about me?

20:40.804 --> 20:42.763
You think I'm --What? No.
No, no, no.

20:42.806 --> 20:44.373
That is --
That's not what I meant.

20:48.769 --> 20:50.379
This is about me.

20:56.603 --> 20:58.257
I won't stop you.

21:01.434 --> 21:03.349
But your sister
probably will.

21:06.917 --> 21:09.006
There's probably
a back way.

21:09.050 --> 21:12.096
[Thunder rumbles]

21:44.520 --> 21:53.137
♪

21:53.181 --> 21:55.096
[Door creaks]

21:55.139 --> 22:00.319
♪

22:00.362 --> 22:02.016
[Door closes]

22:02.059 --> 22:05.846
♪

22:05.889 --> 22:07.978
[Flashlight clicks]

22:08.022 --> 22:16.944
♪

22:16.987 --> 22:18.946
[Sighs]

22:24.212 --> 22:29.391
♪

22:29.435 --> 22:31.175
[Can clatters]

22:31.219 --> 22:39.445
♪

22:39.488 --> 22:43.013
[Footsteps approaching]

22:43.057 --> 22:45.059
Jesus!

22:45.102 --> 22:47.104
Damn.

22:47.148 --> 22:49.324
You were ready to end mewith zero hesitation.

22:49.368 --> 22:51.805
Uh-huh.

22:51.848 --> 22:52.980
What are you
doing here?

22:53.023 --> 22:55.504
Figured
you could use some help.

22:55.548 --> 22:57.288
Where's Felix?

22:57.332 --> 22:59.334
Uh,checking the other side.

22:59.378 --> 23:01.510
I was about to
check upstairs.

23:01.554 --> 23:03.686
Let's go.

23:03.730 --> 23:05.384
You sure?

23:07.342 --> 23:08.343
Wouldn't be here
if I wasn't.

23:08.387 --> 23:10.650
[Walker growling]

23:10.693 --> 23:12.434
Come on.

23:12.478 --> 23:16.612
♪

23:21.661 --> 23:23.402
We were doing fine
by foot.

23:23.445 --> 23:25.491
Slow and sore,
but fine.

23:25.534 --> 23:28.494
Well, anything to get to your
dad faster is worth it, right?

23:28.537 --> 23:31.671
[Thunder rumbles]

23:31.714 --> 23:33.063
You know, I actually
met your dad

23:33.107 --> 23:35.762
before he left
for the Civic Republic.

23:35.805 --> 23:40.375
Went to ask if he would readmy mother's writing, and he did.

23:40.419 --> 23:44.466
He's the one who encouraged me
to finish the manuscript.

23:44.510 --> 23:46.990
Really?
Yeah.

23:47.034 --> 23:48.383
Even though
he'd never met my mom,

23:48.427 --> 23:50.254
he still
admired her research.

23:52.343 --> 23:54.476
He actually kind of
reminded me of her.

23:54.520 --> 23:56.130
Ink stains
on his fingers,

23:56.173 --> 23:59.394
three coffee cups
on his desk, all cold.

23:59.438 --> 24:01.527
It's those little things abouther that I don't want to forget.

24:03.529 --> 24:05.095
Elton...

24:10.797 --> 24:14.496
Maybe we should, uh, focus,i-instead of talking.

24:14.540 --> 24:16.193
Right.

24:27.378 --> 24:36.431
♪

24:36.475 --> 24:39.478
[Walker growling]

24:46.049 --> 24:52.534
♪

24:52.578 --> 24:54.449
[Glass shatters]

24:54.493 --> 24:56.364
[Grunts]

24:56.407 --> 24:58.801
[Breathing heavily]

25:07.331 --> 25:15.644
♪

25:15.688 --> 25:17.820
Hey.

25:57.643 --> 26:07.478
♪

26:07.522 --> 26:10.090
[Water splashes]

26:18.315 --> 26:26.541
♪

26:26.585 --> 26:29.979
[Thunder rumbles]

26:30.023 --> 26:31.633
[Keys jingle]

26:31.677 --> 26:41.556
♪

26:41.600 --> 26:43.950
Hey, hey!

26:43.993 --> 26:45.778
That's my stuff.

26:45.821 --> 26:49.869
♪

26:49.912 --> 26:51.697
Find Felix.Get the car started.

26:51.740 --> 26:53.002
I'll be down in a second.
Don't.

26:53.046 --> 26:54.264
It's not worth --Hey, screw that.

26:54.308 --> 26:55.657
They took my stuff.

26:55.701 --> 26:57.398
I'm taking it back,and I'm taking theirs.

26:57.441 --> 27:02.925
♪

27:02.969 --> 27:04.710
[Door opens]

27:04.753 --> 27:06.233
♪

27:06.276 --> 27:07.974
Hey, Mike --
No, no, no, no, no!

27:08.017 --> 27:09.758
[Gunshot]

27:09.802 --> 27:14.458
♪

27:14.502 --> 27:15.634
What was that?

27:15.677 --> 27:17.026
Maybe
Felix found Mike.

27:17.070 --> 27:18.985
[Walker growling]

27:19.028 --> 27:21.814
♪

27:21.857 --> 27:23.816
[Breathing heavily]

27:23.859 --> 27:29.996
♪

27:30.039 --> 27:31.650
Percy.

27:31.693 --> 27:34.435
♪

27:34.478 --> 27:36.437
[Walker growling]

27:50.799 --> 27:57.893
♪

27:57.937 --> 27:59.634
[Rain falling]

27:59.678 --> 28:01.157
Hope: Maybe we should seeif he's okay.

28:01.201 --> 28:02.550
[Elton grunts]

28:17.739 --> 28:25.225
♪

28:25.268 --> 28:27.227
[Water splashes]

28:27.270 --> 28:35.104
♪

28:35.148 --> 28:37.106
[Walker growling]

28:37.150 --> 28:39.065
[Chain rattling]

28:39.108 --> 28:41.676
♪

28:41.720 --> 28:43.809
[Engine starts]

28:43.852 --> 28:47.508
♪

28:47.551 --> 28:49.075
He's got our stuff!

28:49.118 --> 28:50.772
♪

28:50.816 --> 28:51.991
The dead guy?

28:52.034 --> 28:53.557
My mom's book!
It's in my bag!

28:53.601 --> 28:58.432
♪

28:58.475 --> 29:01.435
[Walker growling]

29:08.659 --> 29:15.754
♪

29:15.797 --> 29:17.886
[Clattering]

29:17.930 --> 29:22.064
♪

29:22.108 --> 29:24.371
Percy!

29:24.414 --> 29:25.851
What...

29:25.894 --> 29:32.945
♪

29:32.988 --> 29:34.598
[Grunts]

29:34.642 --> 29:38.080
♪

29:38.124 --> 29:40.561
Hey!
Hey, stop!

29:40.604 --> 29:42.041
Hey!

29:42.084 --> 29:45.305
Percy: Go, go, go!

29:45.348 --> 29:47.046
Iris: Hope!

29:47.089 --> 29:50.049
♪

29:50.092 --> 29:51.877
Hope: Iris!

29:51.920 --> 29:54.227
Hope?
I can't get out.

29:54.270 --> 29:55.706
The wall's too high.

29:55.750 --> 29:57.752
Don't worry! Felix and Silas
are on their way.

29:57.796 --> 29:58.884
Are you okay?
I'm fine.

29:58.927 --> 30:00.102
I just...

30:00.146 --> 30:01.843
[Rustling]

30:01.887 --> 30:04.106
Iris!
Are you hurt?!

30:04.150 --> 30:05.804
What's wrong?

30:05.847 --> 30:07.370
Iris!

30:07.414 --> 30:09.329
[Growling]

30:09.372 --> 30:16.249
♪

30:16.292 --> 30:17.685
Felix: Iris!
We're here!

30:17.728 --> 30:19.905
We're gonna get you out.

30:19.948 --> 30:20.949
[Growling]

30:20.993 --> 30:21.950
[Screams]

30:21.994 --> 30:22.951
One, two...
Felix!

30:22.995 --> 30:24.344
...three!

30:24.387 --> 30:25.519
Hope: Iris, it's okay!
Just hold on!

30:25.562 --> 30:26.650
Come on!
Keep going!

30:26.694 --> 30:29.218
[Chain rattles]
Help!

30:29.262 --> 30:30.306
Iris, we're in!

30:30.350 --> 30:32.308
Felix, help!

30:32.352 --> 30:33.657
[Walkers growling]

30:33.701 --> 30:36.051
Felix?

30:36.095 --> 30:37.487
Go. Go!

30:37.531 --> 30:38.662
Come on!
Hold them off!

30:38.706 --> 30:41.317
♪

30:41.361 --> 30:42.841
Help!

30:42.884 --> 30:53.068
♪

30:53.112 --> 30:54.243
Iris: Felix!

30:54.287 --> 30:55.810
Felix!

30:55.854 --> 30:57.638
[Yelps]

30:57.681 --> 30:59.509
♪

30:59.553 --> 31:02.208
[Truck approaches]

31:02.251 --> 31:03.557
[Squishing]

31:03.600 --> 31:06.255
Get in!
More has-beens are comin'!

31:06.299 --> 31:08.823
-Come on!
-Let's go!

31:08.867 --> 31:16.439
♪

31:16.483 --> 31:17.919
Come on!

31:24.012 --> 31:30.105
♪

31:37.808 --> 31:41.987
I told ya, kiddo.
No good deed goes unpunished.

31:42.030 --> 31:43.945
What good deed
is that, huh?

31:43.989 --> 31:47.818
You conned us.Yeah, we did.

31:47.862 --> 31:49.777
We came back when we sawthe has-beens comin'.

31:49.820 --> 31:50.952
Hope:I say we take their ride

31:50.996 --> 31:52.519
and leave 'emto become empty chow.

31:52.562 --> 31:54.303
We saved
all your asses!

31:54.347 --> 31:56.392
When we saw the has-beens
comin',

31:56.436 --> 31:57.959
my nephew
had me turn around.

31:58.003 --> 31:59.526
And, what, we should be gratefulthat you robbed us

31:59.569 --> 32:01.049
then changed your mind?

32:01.093 --> 32:03.965
Out here, that's pretty much
as good as it gets.

32:04.009 --> 32:05.967
[Insects chirping]

32:20.416 --> 32:27.554
♪

32:27.597 --> 32:30.122
Keep your eye
on the ball.

32:30.165 --> 32:39.958
♪

32:40.001 --> 32:41.568
It's that one.

32:41.611 --> 32:43.526
[Chuckles]

32:43.570 --> 32:44.788
What? No.

32:44.832 --> 32:47.400
No, no. That's crazy.I know it was there.

32:51.273 --> 32:52.927
Oh!

33:01.936 --> 33:04.417
[Chuckles]

33:04.460 --> 33:06.245
So what?You're a professional scammer.

33:06.288 --> 33:08.073
Young lady,
for 15 years,

33:08.116 --> 33:10.945
I was Tony Delmado,
resident illusionist

33:10.989 --> 33:13.687
at the Pair-a-Dice Lounge
in Las Vegas.

33:13.730 --> 33:16.124
Was your act
all sleight of hand?

33:16.168 --> 33:17.473
An aficionado!

33:17.517 --> 33:18.953
I like it.

33:18.997 --> 33:20.999
Ah, I did
a bit of everything --

33:21.042 --> 33:24.219
illusions, card tricks,
even dabbled in ventriloquism.

33:24.263 --> 33:26.004
Turns out, knowing how
to throw your voice

33:26.047 --> 33:28.745
is quite useful given the state
of the world as it is.

33:28.789 --> 33:32.314
As far as I'm concerned,
I'm still in show business.

33:32.358 --> 33:34.577
For a small fee
at friendly settlements,

33:34.621 --> 33:37.406
we will perform.

33:37.450 --> 33:41.584
That's why the makeup job
is flawless.

33:43.673 --> 33:44.979
And what are you?

33:45.023 --> 33:46.285
His protégé?

33:46.328 --> 33:50.376
Uh, Tony raised me
when my mom split.

33:50.419 --> 33:52.334
Percy's a quick study.

33:52.378 --> 33:54.510
He was grifting kids
in the sandbox.

33:57.209 --> 34:01.343
Uh, it -- it's how we get what
we need without hurting people.

34:01.387 --> 34:03.563
[Chuckles]

34:03.606 --> 34:05.130
Wow.

34:05.173 --> 34:07.436
You guys deserve medals
or somethin'.

34:12.702 --> 34:14.530
[Water flowing]

34:14.574 --> 34:16.619
[Birds chirping]

34:29.937 --> 34:31.547
Hey.

34:37.901 --> 34:40.774
Ya gonna stay mad
at me forever?

34:40.817 --> 34:44.125
Forever?

34:44.169 --> 34:46.867
It's cool, you don't have tokeep pretending you care.

34:46.910 --> 34:48.564
That's kinda cynical.
I don't take you for a cynic.

34:48.608 --> 34:51.350
No, you take mefor everything I'm worth.

34:57.573 --> 34:59.184
Know what
the worst part is?

35:01.664 --> 35:04.232
I really thoughtI had good instincts.

35:08.367 --> 35:10.195
You do.

35:12.545 --> 35:16.592
You came back up those stairs
to help me.

35:16.636 --> 35:20.640
See, I -- I've probably run
this grift a dozen times,

35:20.683 --> 35:23.904
and people always
take the keys and run.

35:23.947 --> 35:25.471
But you didn't.

35:25.514 --> 35:27.429
♪

35:27.473 --> 35:28.691
What does that have
to do with --

35:28.735 --> 35:30.389
You saw me as
someone worth saving.

35:30.432 --> 35:32.739
♪

35:32.782 --> 35:34.306
That's why
I came back.

35:34.349 --> 35:36.482
♪

35:36.525 --> 35:38.179
'Cause that's who
I wanted to be.

35:43.271 --> 35:48.363
♪

35:48.407 --> 35:51.758
I, uh...

35:51.801 --> 35:54.500
I guess it's on me now to prove
I can be more like you.

36:11.343 --> 36:19.655
♪

36:19.699 --> 36:22.528
Hey.

36:22.571 --> 36:25.705
You know, I'd love to readyour mom's book sometime.

36:25.748 --> 36:27.315
If you'd let me.

36:29.883 --> 36:31.101
You would?

36:31.145 --> 36:33.234
Yeah, absolutely.

36:33.278 --> 36:42.504
♪

36:42.548 --> 36:48.075
I might be the only person left
in the world who saw her,

36:48.118 --> 36:49.685
who knew her.

36:49.729 --> 36:52.862
But...

36:52.906 --> 36:55.082
at least now someone else
will know her, too.

37:14.275 --> 37:23.763
♪

37:23.806 --> 37:25.765
[Tools clanking]

37:25.808 --> 37:31.597
♪

37:31.640 --> 37:34.774
We need to talk.

37:34.817 --> 37:36.297
As we say in my business,

37:36.341 --> 37:38.560
we got ourselves a setup,

37:38.604 --> 37:40.519
but no punch line.

37:40.562 --> 37:42.042
We both want the truck,

37:42.085 --> 37:45.785
but only I know
where to get more fuel.

37:45.828 --> 37:49.963
This isn't as much ofa conversation as it is, what?

37:50.006 --> 37:51.747
You trying to play me?

37:51.791 --> 37:53.619
Threaten me?

37:53.662 --> 37:54.924
My nephew
promised you a ride,

37:54.968 --> 37:56.230
and I intend
to make good on that.

37:56.274 --> 37:58.841
But first,
I want to know about

37:58.885 --> 38:01.453
that fetching insignia
you got there.

38:01.496 --> 38:03.324
What, this?

38:03.368 --> 38:06.719
It's, uh, the emblem ofthe University where we live.

38:09.896 --> 38:12.986
As the saying goes,
don't bullshit a bullshitter.

38:13.029 --> 38:14.857
Especially
one from Vegas.

38:21.386 --> 38:23.431
I know whatever group's behind
this doesn't mess around,

38:23.475 --> 38:25.128
and they're close.

38:25.172 --> 38:27.653
I've seen helicopters
flying around with this symbol.

38:27.696 --> 38:30.482
♪

38:30.525 --> 38:33.485
If it's so dangerous,why not leave?

38:33.528 --> 38:35.313
Let's just say
it's a good thing

38:35.356 --> 38:37.619
I checked the driver's pockets
when we searched the truck.

38:37.663 --> 38:42.276
Found something that pointed us
to a refueling station nearby.

38:42.320 --> 38:44.800
Now we got a routine down
on how to get what we need

38:44.844 --> 38:47.455
and avoid these assholes.

38:47.499 --> 38:49.065
You didn't avoid us.

38:49.109 --> 38:50.632
You're not them.

38:50.676 --> 38:52.634
They're armed to the hilt
in all-black uniforms.

38:52.678 --> 38:56.638
You're a ragtag group of kids
in homemade leather.

38:56.682 --> 38:59.293
What I want to know is,
if we get into a bind,

38:59.337 --> 39:01.861
can that patch of yours
get us out?

39:01.904 --> 39:05.168
♪

39:05.212 --> 39:07.040
Of course it can.

39:07.083 --> 39:08.694
♪

39:08.737 --> 39:12.306
Great. Then tomorrow, we pick upyour friend and we ride.

39:12.350 --> 39:16.005
To wherever
you want to go.

39:16.049 --> 39:18.312
But first,

39:18.356 --> 39:20.009
a little entertainment.

39:22.447 --> 39:25.101
[Fire crackling]

39:40.552 --> 39:43.076
Some people make it
look so easy.

39:43.119 --> 39:44.773
What?

39:44.817 --> 39:47.428
Starting over.

39:47.472 --> 39:51.214
Mm.
Yeah.

39:51.258 --> 39:56.219
I wish I knew which part of himwas the lie

39:56.263 --> 39:57.830
and which part was real.

39:57.873 --> 40:00.006
You know?

40:00.049 --> 40:02.835
He's the same as us.

40:02.878 --> 40:06.099
We all have parts
that we want people to see,

40:06.142 --> 40:10.146
and parts of us
that we try to hide.

40:10.190 --> 40:11.800
It's all real.

40:18.416 --> 40:21.070
Ladies and gentlemen,without further ado...

40:21.114 --> 40:24.073
We welcome you to the end
of the world.

40:26.032 --> 40:29.949
<i>["Here Comes the River"
playing]</i>

40:29.992 --> 40:34.214
♪ <i>The windows turned
to fishbowls♪</i>

40:34.257 --> 40:36.608
♪ <i>The cities to seas</i>♪

40:36.651 --> 40:38.566
♪

40:38.610 --> 40:41.395
♪ <i>The cars were drownin'</i>♪

40:41.439 --> 40:43.092
♪ <i>Underneath your feet</i>♪

40:43.136 --> 40:47.227
♪

40:47.270 --> 40:49.272
♪ <i>The children were swimming</i>♪

40:49.316 --> 40:51.274
♪

40:51.318 --> 40:53.451
♪ <i>From the top of the trees</i>♪

40:53.494 --> 40:56.062
♪

40:56.105 --> 41:01.067
♪ <i>Crowds of umbrellas
were starin' in misbelief♪</i>

41:01.110 --> 41:04.679
♪

